        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 1 at 4:10PM CDT by NWS San Angelo TX</headline>
        <description>At 408 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking scattered strong
thunderstorms from eastern McCulloch County, south through Mason
County, and into eastern Kimble County. All storms had slow and
variable movement.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Brady, Mason, Art, Brady Lake, Fredonia, Yates Crossing, Segovia,
Camp San Saba, Streeter, Hedwigs Hill, Camp Air, Hilda, Long
Mountain, Calf Creek, Grit, Katemcy, London, and Voca.

This includes Interstate 10 between Mile Markers 465 and 477.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
